y:Films set in the 19th century]]\n[[Category:Motion capture in film]]\n[[Category:Rotoscoped films]]\n[[Category:Polish films]]\n[[Category:Polish animated films]]\n[[Category:Polish avant-garde and experimental films]]\n[[Category:Films about Vincent van Gogh]]\n[[Category:Kickstarter-funded films]]\n[[Category:2010s avant-garde and experimental films]]\n", "name_user": "Edwin of Northumbria", "label": "safe", "comment": "Minor rewording.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loving_Vincent"}
{"title_page": "Casey Mongillo", "text_new": "{{short description|American voice actor}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Casey Mongillo\n| image        = Casey Mongillo.jpg\n| caption      = \n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1987|10|22}}<ref name=:1>{{Cite web|title= Casey MONGOLLIO-Anime News Network|access-date=April 5, 2020|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/encyclopedia/people.php?id=74826}}</ref>\n| birth_place  = [[Hartford, Connecticut]], U.S.<ref name=\"linkedin\">{{cite web | url=https://www.linkedin.com/in/caseymongillo?trk=public_profile_browsemap_profile-result-card_result-card_full-click | title=Casey Mongillo | work=[[LinkedIn]] | accessdate=October 21, 2019 | url-access=registration }}</ref>\n| occupation   = Voice actor\n| years_active = 2006&ndash;present\n| website      = {{url|www.caseymongillo.com}}\n}}\n<!-- Please do not change the they/them pronouns without first discussing it on the talk page. Thanks. --> \n'''Casey Mongillo'''  (born October 22, 1987)<ref name=:1/>is an American [[voice actor]] who has played roles in [[animation]] and [[video games]]. Mongillo is best known for portraying lead character [[Shinji Ikari]] in the [[Netflix]] English dub of ''[[Neon Genesis Evangelion]]'' in 2019, for which they received critical acclaim. They also played Shou Suzuki in the [[dub localization|dub]] of the ''[[Mob Psycho 100]]'' anime.\n\n==Career==\nIn 2019, Mongillo voiced the main character [[Shinji Ikari]] in the [[Netflix]] dub of the [[anime]] series ''[[Neon Genesis Evangelion]]'', replacing [[Spike Spencer]], who played the part in the original [[ADV Films]] dub.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://slate.com/culture/2019/06/netflix-has-upset-evangelion-fans-are-with-changes-to-the-series.html|title=Anime Classic Neon Genesis Evangelion Is Finally on Netflix. So Why Are Some Fans Upset?|work=[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]]|access-date=November 3, 2019|date=June 28, 2019|first=Eric|last=Vilas-Boas|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009225140/https://slate.com/culture/2019/06/netflix-has-upset-evangelion-fans-are-with-changes-to-the-series.html|archive-date=October 9, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"tvguide\"/> Mongillo tweeted that playing Shinji was \"one of the greatest honors of my life\".<ref name=\"tweet\">{{Cite tweet |number=1141998448972976128 |user=CaseyTheVA |title=It's one of the greatest honors of my life to have portrayed Shinji Ikari in Neon Genesis Evangelion for Netflix's English dub. |first=Casey |last=Mongillo |date=June 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\nNoel Kirkpatrick of ''[[TV Guide]]'' praised Mongillo's portrayal of Shinji, saying they excelled at switching \"between sarcasm and sadness, delight and detachment\", and that they did \"a better job of capturing Shinji's pre-teen voice\" than Spencer.<ref name=\"tvguide\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/neon-genesis-evangelion-netflix-review/ |title=What Netflix Got Right and Wrong About Its Neon Genesis Evangelion Release |work=[[TV Guide]] |first=Noel |last=Kirkpatrick |date=June 24, 2019 |access-date=July 2, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629015643/https://www.tvguide.com/news/neon-genesis-evangelion-netflix-review/ |archive-date=June 29, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Aja Romano of ''[[Vox (website)|Vox]]'' wrote that it was laudable that Netflix cast a non-binary actor to play Shinji.<ref name=\"Vox\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.vox.com/culture/2019/6/24/18701179/netflix-neon-genesis-evangelion-kaworu-gay-backlash |title=Netflix\u2019s re-translation of Neon Genesis Evangelion is drawing backlash for queer erasure |work=Vox |access-date=November 3, 2019 |first=Aja |last=Romano |date=June 24, 2019 |8= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190701102316/https://www.vox.com/culture/2019/6/24/18701179/netflix-neon-genesis-evangelion-kaworu-gay-backlash |archive-date=July 1, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Carol Grant, in an opinion piece for ''[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]]'', wrote that Shinji being played by a [[transgender|trans]] actor made the series feel more [[queer]], saying that \"Mongillo's delivery captures the delicate interplay between the masculine and feminine aspects of Shinji's voice and personality, bringing his bodily and gendered anxieties to life\".<ref name=\"Vice\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/neap3g/neon-genesis-evangelion-feels-more-explicitly-queer-thanks-to-this-trans-voice-actor-netflix |title='Neon Genesis Evangelion' Feels More Explicitly Queer Thanks to This Trans Voice Actor |last=Grant |first=Carol |date=July 12, 2019 |work=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] |language=en-US |access-date=July 17, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190717030707/https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/neap3g/neon-genesis-evangelion-feels-more-explicitly-queer-thanks-to-this-trans-voice-actor-netflix |archive-date=July 17, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nMongillo was nominated for Best Performance by a Voice Actor (English) in the [[Crunchyroll Anime Awards]] for their performance as Shinji.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.animationmagazine.net/events/nominees-announced-for-crunchyroll-anime-awards-vote-now/ |title=Nominees Announced for Crunchyroll Anime Awards, Vote Now! |last=Milligan |first=Mercedes |date=2020-01-10 |website=Animation Magazine |language=en-US |access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2020/01/10/meet-the-nominees-for-this-years-anime-awards |title=Meet the Nominees for This Year\u2019s Anime Awards! |last=Coats |first=Cayla |website=Crunchyroll.com |language=en-us |access-date=2020-02-13}}</ref>\n\nMongillo released a single, \"Everything Is Alright\", on [[Apple Music]] on April 3, 2012.<ref name=\"single\" />\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Anime ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" |Notes\n! class=\"unsortable\" |Source<ref name=\"Resume 1\">{{cite web|title=Casey Mongillo Animation Roles|url=ht